Assistant
Assistant object is defined as follows: A COVID-19 test assistant is someone related to the university (staff or student) who is volunteering to perform COVID tests. To register an assistant in the system, you need their university email and a non-blank name. The email must be unique and follow the pattern “*@uok.ac.uk”. Print template: | name | email |

Booking
A booking consists of matching a bookable room and an assistant on shift at a specific time-slot to perform a COVID-19 test on a student.
BookingApp
Starting conditions: 3 rooms 3 assistants 9 bookable room 6 assistants on shift Create bookings such that: The system has at least one booking SCHEDULED and one COMPLETED. The system has at least one bookable room FULL, one AVAILABLE, and one EMPTY. The system has at least one assistant on shift FREE and one BUSY.

Room
Room object is defined as follows: The university has several rooms, and some of the rooms can be allocated to apply COVID tests. A room must have a string code (e.g., IC215) and a capacity. The code is used to identify the room and, therefore, must be unique. The capacity must be an integer value greater than zero.

University
University object is defined as follows: The University has a list of assistants and a list of rooms. You should implement functions to add, both assistants and rooms. Due to time constraints, you don’t need to develop screen to manage the university resources, but you need to pre-load the system with instances of rooms and assistants.
